It seems like the tasks are not displaying properly because of the missing `subtasks` property when creating a new task. The following changes are required to fix the issue:

1. Modify the `handleAddTask` function in the `TaskInput` component to include a unique `id` for each task and an empty `subtasks` array:

```javascript
const handleAddTask = () => {
  if (taskTitle && taskType) {
    const newTask = {
      id: Date.now(),
      title: taskTitle,
      type: taskType,
      subtasks: [],
    };
    onAddTask(newTask);
    setTaskTitle('');
    setTaskType('');
  }
};
```

2. Update the `onAddSubtask` and `updateSubtaskStatus` function calls in the `SubtaskModal` component to include the `taskId`:

```javascript
const handleAddSubtask = () => {
  if (subtaskTitle) {
    const newSubtask = { id: Date.now(), title: subtaskTitle, status: 0 };
    onAddSubtask(task.id, newSubtask);
    setSubtaskTitle('');
  }
};
```

```javascript
<Subtask
  key={subtask.id}
  taskId={task.id}
  subtask={subtask}
/>
```

After these changes, the tasks should display correctly below Front-End Tasks or Back-End Tasks.

