To change the webpack watch mode settings in Quasar PWA, you can follow the below steps:

1. Open the `quasar.conf.js` file located in the root directory of your project.
2. Look for the `build` property and then `extendWebpack` property inside it.
3. Add the `watchOptions` property with your desired configuration. For example:

   ```
   extendWebpack(cfg) {
      cfg.watchOptions = {
         ignored: /node_modules/,
         poll: 1000
      };
   }
   ```

   In this example, we added `ignored` and `poll` configuration options to the `watchOptions` property.

4. Save the file and restart your development server.

Note: The `watchOptions` property is an object that accepts various values to configure the webpack watch mode. You can refer to the webpack documentation for more details on the available options.

If you are only using `quasar dev` and not building your app for production, you don't need to modify the `quasar.conf.js` file. The service worker (`generateSW`) is only generated during the production build process and will not be used during development.

Therefore, you can simply ignore the service worker generated during development as it will be overwritten when you generate the service worker during production builds.

However, if you want to disable the service worker in development mode, you can add the following code to your `src/index.template.html` file to prevent the service worker from being registered:

```
<script>
  if ('serviceWorker' in navigator) {
    navigator.serviceWorker.ready
      .then(registration => {
        registration.unregister();
      });
  }
</script>
```

Keep in mind that this will only disable the service worker during development and will not affect the production build.

